Hyperdynamics Plans to Invest $70 Million in Drilling in Guinea, CEO Says

-- B y   O u g n a   C a m a r a
-- 
2011-05-12T01:39:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/hyperdynamics-plans-to-invest-70-million-in-drilling-in-guinea-ceo-says.html
Hyperdynamics Corp. (HDY)  plans to invest
$70 million to drill in  Guinea  for first time in October, Chief
Executive Officer Ray Leonard said.  “The company launched 2D and 3D seismic surveys,” Leonard
said during a presentation at a mining conference in Conakry.
Hyperdynamics has “collected $192 million to finance the
explorations by 2D and 3D.”  “We are very enthusiastic on the offshore potential of
Guinea,” he said.  For Related News and Information:  To contact the reporter on this story:
